"notes": [
"The circuit caption is "Figure 1. Standard Application Circuit" and the IC shown is MAX757.",
"Junction(U1-8,L1,D1) is an inferred switching node connecting the MAX757 LX pin, the inductor, and the rectifier diode.",
"Junction(U1-3,C3) is an inferred reference-bypass node; C3 provides REF bypassing to GND.",
"Junction(U1-2,R1,R2) is an inferred feedback node; R1 and R2 form the output-voltage divider between VOUT and GND into FB.",
"Junction(U1-5,R3,R4) is an inferred low-battery sense node; R3 and R4 form the input-voltage divider between VIN and GND into LBI.",
"U1 pin 1 (SHDN) is marked NC because only the descriptive pin/signal role is visible with no explicit external component or net connection shown; intended role is the shutdown control input.",
"U1 pin 4 (LBO) is marked NC because only the descriptive pin/signal role is visible with no explicit external component or net connection shown; intended role is the low-battery open-drain output.",
"C1 is the input reservoir/bypass capacitor from VIN to GND, and C2 is the output filter capacitor from VOUT to GND.",
"D1 is the boost rectifier from the LX switching node to VOUT."
]
}
